ht|d|cp||at|^aHere is Howard's feeling about maximal doubles. They are a nice convention but can be confusing if not well understood. In particular, you have to understand they only apply over 3@d when your suit is hearts and over 3@h when your suit is spades. Thus, for example, on the auction 1@s-2@d-2@s-3@d-dbl, the double is not maximal. Note that 3@s over 3@d is still a competitive bid, not a game try. You can make a game try  over 3@d by bidding 3@h. As to whether you should play them or not. I tried them and no longer play them with many of my expert partners. I don't particularly miss them. If you want to play them, I think that is fine. But I don't think you should go out of your way to play them, especially with partners who tend to forget conventions or are easily confused.|
