at|^^|cp||at|^a|
at|^^|cp||at|^aAs to Cohen's contention that "all doubles at the 1-level and 2-level are not penalty", I don't agree with that. In particular, I have been very successful in match points at doubling opponents at the 2-level vulnerable. Beating them 1 for +200 is usually a top board. I have found that, because the modern style is to compete vigorously, opponents often get overly aggressive and bid poor 4-card suits at the 2-level when they should not. When I have length and strength in their suit, I am very willing to double them. So if a double is not takeout, negative, support, or responsive (assuming you play responsive doubles), assume it is penalty even at the 1-level and 2-level. Having said that, I will say that most experts agree with Cohen.|
